citeinfo.title: Monarch Conservation Science Partnership: Monarch Data - County Summaries

descript.abstract: The geometry for this data set is taken from the 2014 U.S.. Department of Commerce, U.S. Census Bureau, Geography Division counties data set. Several inportant spatial data sets attribute information were either appended to this layer's attribute table (if already summarized to the county scale) or the underlying data set was summarized spatially to the county scale (i.e., land cover/land use).
descript.purpose: This spatial data set (shapefile) was developed to be used in the prioritization of counties within the contimerous United States with respect to Monarch butterfly conservation. This shapefile is meant to be used as the input data layer in the County Ranking Tool within the Monarch Conservation Planning Tools ArcGIS 10.3 toolbox.
descript.supplinf: The input data itself spans from 1992 (USGS pesticide data) to 2014 (CRP, etc)
